other_tests.findings: Hypoattenuation of the liver is compatible with fatty infiltration. Focal fat stranding around sigmoid colonic diverticula. A 4 mm nonobstructing right interpolar renal calculus is noted. No extraluminal air or drainable fluid collection. No pathologically enlarged lymph nodes are seen.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Segment III and VI hypodensities have been previously characterized as a cyst on prior MRI.
